"n.葡萄糖 【记】 gluco (葡萄糖)+se→葡萄糖 n. 葡萄糖(一种单糖, 广见于大多数动植物组织, 是血液中基本的循环糖和人体等主要能量来源) 【记】源自希腊语gleukos甜酒－葡萄糖glu = glue胶水, cose读: 酷似: 胶水酷似葡萄糖 【记】glue 胶 + 音：可食，一种胶是葡萄糖浓缩的液体，以前有种可以吃的胶状物叫糖稀，也是胶体 glucose (n.)  1840, from French glucose (1838), said to have been coined by French professor Eugène Melchior Péligot (1811-1890) from Greek gleukos ""must, sweet wine,"" related to glykys ""sweet, delightful, dear,"" from *glku-, dissimilated in Greek from PIE *dlk-u- ""sweet"" (source also of Latin dulcis). It first was obtained from grape sugar."
